<title>UK: Leeds Group makes provision for job cuts.</title>
<headline>Leeds Group makes provision for job cuts.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-11-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Leeds Group Plc said on Thursday it would take a 2.5 million stg charge in its second half accounts for redundancy costs and an asset write-down.  </p>
<p>Leeds said it would cut 65 jobs at its fabric dyeing division, Scott &amp; Rhodes, and will close its Leonard Ingham unit which employs 34 people.</p>
<p>Leeds has already announced staff reductions at its textiles printing unit, Strines.</p>
<p>The company said it expects to announce its results for the year to September 30 on December 10. -- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7717.</p>
